<h1>Hammerfel</h1>

<a href="hammerfel_archive.jsp">View The Hammerfel Archive</a>





<h2>EverQuest Web Teaser Walk-through</h2>
<P>The holidays started a few days early this year for EverQuest fans curious about what's next for their favorite online game.&nbsp; The rumors on the Web were rampant, with expansion titles and storyline theories being passed back and forth across fan sites.&nbsp; It was not until Friday evening, December 20th,that the mystery began to unfold with the release of a new EverQuest.com front page.</P>
<P><STRONG>Step 1: The Rune in the Clouds<BR></STRONG>Floating in the clouds of the EverQuest banner on the new EverQuest.com page, astute readers noticed an odd rune.&nbsp; Clicking on the rune brought up a Flash tableau consisting of 29 rune-etched stone tiles.&nbsp; </P>
<P>
<OBJECT codeBase=http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,29,0 height=343 width=561 classid=clsid:D27CDB6E-AE6D-11cf-96B8-444553540000><PARAM NAME="_cx" VALUE="14843"><PARAM NAME="_cy" VALUE="9075"><PARAM NAME="FlashVars" VALUE="14843"><PARAM NAME="Movie" VALUE="http://everquest.station.sony.com/assembler/loader_hints.swf"><PARAM NAME="Src" VALUE="http://everquest.station.sony.com/assembler/loader_hints.swf"><PARAM NAME="WMode" VALUE="Opaque"><PARAM NAME="Play" VALUE="0"><PARAM NAME="Loop" VALUE="-1"><PARAM NAME="Quality" VALUE="High"><PARAM NAME="SAlign" VALUE=""><PARAM NAME="Menu" VALUE="-1"><PARAM NAME="Base" VALUE=""><PARAM NAME="AllowScriptAccess" VALUE="always"><PARAM NAME="Scale" VALUE="ShowAll"><PARAM NAME="DeviceFont" VALUE="0"><PARAM NAME="EmbedMovie" VALUE="0"><PARAM NAME="BGColor" VALUE=""><PARAM NAME="SWRemote" VALUE="">
				 
		<embed src="http://everquest.station.sony.com/assembler/loader_hints.swf" quality="high" pluginspage="http://www.macromedia.com/go/getflashplayer" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="561" height="343"></embed></OBJECT></P>
<P>At the bottom of the tableau were six empty slots.&nbsp; Each rune tile had an ancient Troll pronunciation associated with it (courtesy of one senior editor's surprisingly versatile vocal cords).&nbsp; Throughout the weekend, players could fiddle with this "assembler" and see what they could discover.</P>
<P>There were several "red herrings" in the puzzle, many being the very rumors that had circulated on the Web:</P>
<P><EM>"Kingdom of Serellis"</EM><BR><EM>"Lost Dungeons of Norrath"</EM></P>
<P>After <A href="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/forums/showthread.php?s=&amp;threadid=13655">a clever player</A> assembled <EM>"Kingdom of Hammerfel,"</EM> which turned out to be a coincidental phrase, it was included as a red herring as well,&nbsp;leading the player to the Hammerfel section of EverQuestLive.com.</P>
<P><STRONG>Step 2:&nbsp; Rune Scrambles<BR></STRONG>The correct combination to the puzzle arrived piecemeal in random players' email inboxes on Monday, December 23rd, via the EQ newsletter.&nbsp; </P>
<P>Spoon-feeding was definitely not the order of the day, however, and players had to put their puzzle solving skills to work on another set of puzzles:&nbsp; reassembling the six correct runic tiles that had been cut up and scrambled, ` la the Station.com game, Confetti.</P>
<P>The six scrambled rune puzzles are located at these addresses:</P>
<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">
<P>Rune 1:<BR>Puzzle: <A href="http://everquest.station.sony.com/091265/er41234.jsp">http://everquest.station.sony.com/091265/er41234.jsp</A><BR>Results: <A href="http://everquest.station.sony.com/091265/yig198214.jsp">http://everquest.station.sony.com/091265/yig198214.jsp</A></P>
<P>Rune 2:<BR>Puzzle: <A href="http://everquest.station.sony.com/096512/g871243.jsp">http://everquest.station.sony.com/096512/g871243.jsp</A><BR>Results:&nbsp; <A href="http://everquest.station.sony.com/096512/iah124308.jsp">http://everquest.station.sony.com/096512/iah124308.jsp</A></P>
<P>Rune 3:<BR>Puzzle: <A href="http://everquest.station.sony.com/120965/j87642.jsp">http://everquest.station.sony.com/120965/j87642.jsp</A><BR>Results:&nbsp; <A href="http://everquest.station.sony.com/120965/oiuwq214.jsp">http://everquest.station.sony.com/120965/oiuwq214.jsp</A></P>
<P>Rune 4:<BR>Puzzle:&nbsp; <A href="http://everquest.station.sony.com/126509/we1674.jsp">http://everquest.station.sony.com/126509/we1674.jsp</A><BR>Results:&nbsp; <A href="http://everquest.station.sony.com/126509/mwjrt271.jsp">http://everquest.station.sony.com/126509/mwjrt271.jsp</A></P>
<P>Rune 5:<BR>Puzzle:&nbsp; <A href="http://everquest.station.sony.com/650912/ido70792.jsp">http://everquest.station.sony.com/650912/ido70792.jsp</A><BR>Results:&nbsp; <A href="http://everquest.station.sony.com/650912/ljrtd9436.jsp">http://everquest.station.sony.com/650912/ljrtd9436.jsp</A></P>
<P>Rune 6:<BR>Puzzle:&nbsp; <A href="http://everquest.station.sony.com/651209/12fasdf.jsp">http://everquest.station.sony.com/651209/12fasdf.jsp</A><BR>Results:&nbsp; <A href="http://everquest.station.sony.com/651209/986saous.jsp">http://everquest.station.sony.com/651209/986saous.jsp</A></P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><STRONG>Step 3:&nbsp; The Troll Speaks<BR></STRONG>Once players had all six of the correct runes at their disposal, they could return to the assembler and begin arranging the correct tiles into some sensible order.&nbsp; When placed in the correct order, consecutive pronunciation of the symbols resulted in "Prophesy of Grozmok."&nbsp; The correct tiles would merge into one then rise to the top of the tableau; below it, the next step of the puzzle was revealed:</P>
<P><EM>"Seek the Prophesy of Grozmok"</EM></P>
<P><STRONG>Step 4:&nbsp; Where Have I Heard That Before?<BR></STRONG>The "Prophesy of Grozmok" refers to lore stored in the great library on the Plane of Knowledge.&nbsp; The lore recounts the Troll myth and the turbulent history of "The Grozmok" as written in blood by the shamans of ages past on the revered Troll artifact, the "Stone Frum Pazt."</P>
<P>Players, especially those who participated in our last teaser, eventually tried <A href="http://www.prophecyofgrozmok.com/">www.prophecyofgrozmok.com</A>, and arrived at a new puzzle page, the final step toward the solution.</P>
<P><STRONG>Step 5:&nbsp; What Is "the Grozmok"?<BR></STRONG>The final puzzle featured a screenshot of the great library on the Plane of Knowledge surrounded by a series of runes in a different style from the more crude Trollish tiles.&nbsp; At the bottom of the puzzle lay just three empty slots and the question:&nbsp; "What is 'The Grozmok'?" </P>
<P>The screenshot is a clue in this section of the teaser, and it sent players diving into the game to do the research on Troll history.&nbsp;&nbsp;For those who read the in-game lore,&nbsp;they could find a word in the&nbsp;library text that&nbsp;fit quite nicely into the three tile slots, spelled with a few flips and proper placement of the tiles.&nbsp; This unlocked the final solution.</P>
<P><STRONG>A Big Thanks to the Community<BR></STRONG>These kinds of teaser games are a lot of fun to make, and you guys always surprise us with your ingenuity.&nbsp; The speed at which you figure these out is amazing.&nbsp; </P>
<P>A special thanks to the fan sites for their forums and their enthusiastic participation in these teasers.&nbsp; Without your meeting places for players, we couldn't pull off interactive teasers like this.</P>
<P>Here are some of the discussion threads from the community:</P>
<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">
<P><A href="http://boards.stratics.com/php-bin/eq/showflat.php?Cat=&amp;Board=eqwestwood&amp;Number=757046&amp;page=0&amp;view=collapsed&amp;sb=5&amp;o=0&amp;fpart=all&amp;what2=postlist">EQ Stratics</A><BR><A href="http://pub146.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showMessage?topicID=26153.topic">The Safehouse</A><BR><A href="http://pub149.ezboard.com/feqdruids24038frm1.showMessage?topicID=2770.topic">EQ Druids</A><BR><A href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessage?topicID=23822.topic">Graffe's Wizard Compilation</A>&nbsp; <BR><A href="http://forums.shadowknight.org/showthread.php?s=c89553dec42c03189d66d06d372b50d3&amp;threadid=9551">ShadowKnight.org</A>&nbsp; <BR><A href="http://pub148.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showMessage?topicID=17415.topic">Paladins of Norrath</A>&nbsp; <BR><A href="http://pub149.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showMessage?topicID=29913.topic">Druids Grove</A><BR><A href="http://pub147.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showMessage?topicID=16095.topic">The Concert Hall</A>&nbsp; <BR><A href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showMessage?topicID=2668.topic">The Steel Warrior</A>&nbsp; <BR><A href="http://forums.interealms.com/ranger/showthread.php?s=&amp;threadid=15793">The Ranger's Glade</A><BR><A href="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/forums/showthread.php?s=&amp;threadid=13655">EQ Cleric Forums</A></P>
<P>Special thanks to Glip, Malachite and Fatal for their assistance. :)</P></BLOCKQUOTE>



